Description:
Keeping your data safe, findable and re-usable is essential to good research. Planning this from the start helps not only the sharing of data in the longer-term, but ensures that it is available for you as the primary researcher to find and use as you begin to write up your thesis or article.

All 1st year PhDs are required to create a Data Management Plan (DMP).

This 45 minute lecture will:
-Explain the DMP template that all 1st year PhDs are required to complete and lodge with their 1st year report in PGR Tracker
-Time will be given to explain the purpose of the DMP, including why it is important for those researchers who may not traditionally consider that they have data
-Focus on the different sections in the DMP

At the end of the briefing you should:
-Be aware of the DMP template and where to find it
-Know the principles behind each section
-Be able to complete your DMP
